header.gameNote: WCC MEN'S TOURNAMENT - QUARTERFINALS AT LAS VEGAS NV

article.description: Marc Trasolini scored 22 points and Kevin Foster added 18 to break Santa Clara's single-season scoring record in a 76-68 victory Saturday night over Loyola Marymount.
article.headline: Loyola falls to Santa Clara in WCC quarterfinals
article.linkText: Loyola falls to Santa Clara in WCC quarterfinals
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Marc Trasolini scored 22 points and Kevin Foster added 18 to break Santa Clara's single-season scoring record in a 76-68 victory Saturday night over Loyola Marymount in the West Coast Conference tournament quarterfinals. Santa Clara (19-13), the fourth seed, will face No. 1 seed Saint Mary's in a semifinal on Sunday. Freshman Anthony Ireland led Loyola Marymount with a career-high 24 points. The Lions blew any hopes they had of pulling off a second consecutive upset by making only 14 of 29 free throws. Santa Clara made nine more, hitting 23 of 29, for the win.
